('adef174a-4eb4-420c-9685-41e04a09c732', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'dresden', NULL, 'Worldwide more than 51 million people are on the run, and because of this humanitarian catastrophe, HELLERAU -European Center for the Arts has taken a small group of asylum seekers. Together with\r\n them and refugees from other centers, the volunteer efforts of the neighborhood and cooperation with various NGOs, an intercultural park on the fallow green areas  behind the Festspielhaus started: the Golgi Park. The goal of this park is to start a place for intercultural meetings and an ecological exchange with artistic programs and to help refugees with social involvement. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '56598db43b609', 'en', '2017-03-20 14:01:23', '2017-03-20 14:01:23', 'The Golgi Park is meeting place made by refugees and volunteers in the European Center of the Arts in Hellerau. The focus point on the meeting is ecological and artistic projects.', NULL),
